Daily illustration on smokers, cigarettes, tobacco and smoking in general. JOHANNESBURG - The Fair Trade Independent Tobacco Association is taking legal action against government over their about-turn on tobacco regulation. It filed papers a short while ago. President Cyril Ramaphosa had initially said tobacco products could be sold during level four of the lockdown. But that decision was later reversed. READ: British American Tobacco sets deadline for government to revoke ban The Presidency is standing firm saying its decision is based on advice from experts. “The president and all ministers act on the basis of collective decision...There is no reason why the president or cabinet cannot change their minds...There was a strong feeling that lifting the tobacco ban will not be helpful...Those are issues that will be ventilated in the correspondence that the government will send through in response to letters by interested parties,” said the president’s spokesperson, Kusela Diko. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 11